<br>
  Now, the water pet takes less damage then the earth pet due it having more dex then the earth.  He also seems to deal roughly the same amount of damage as the earth.  I know earth has a max dmg a whole 2 points higher then water but he doesn't hit for max the entire time.  When you look at the average dmg done by earth, he is not going to be that much higher then water if any higher at all.  Another thing is that water does regen hitpoints faster then earth. Almost double that of earths regen.  This, usually, allows for your pet to take on more monsters before needing to resummon a new one.  IE: you probably will have enough mana for a extra nuke now and then due to more medding time. (I am thinking that you will probably be medding while watching the fight after pulling the mob, I could be wrong but it just seems like the sane thing to do since the pet can easily handle the mob). Which in the end another nuke here and then equals a faster kill and a pet with more health, which also allows your pet to handle another mob maybe.<br>
<br>
Now, basicly we are just splitting hairs here.  Either pet you use your going to have more then enough mana the whole time it's just a matter of how many monsters per pet you can get out of each pet and how fast of a kill each one does.  Based on lots of playing around in oot while leveling this is what i figure is the list best to worst for soloing here, and a lot of other solo places.<br>
<br>
1. lvl 54 Water pet<br>
2. lvl 50 MSII pet<br>
3. lvl 51 Earth pet<br>
4. lvl 49 Fire pet<br>
5. a tie between lvl 49 earth pet and lvl 53 air pet<br>
6. every other 49 pet<br>
7. every 44 pet<br>
8. maybe the 52 fire pet.<br>
<br>
But anyways, as I said we are basicly just spliting hairs between the top pets.  I just first posted cause the thread said Water pet is useless which of course it is not.<br>
